**Grading notes:** a real graded attempt (1/2) wrote `{"type": keyword}` without quotes around `"keyword"` — invalid JSON. Field type values are always quoted strings.

```json
GET /events/_search
{
  "query": {
    "bool": {
      "must": [
        { "match": { "foul_type": "card" } },
        { "match": { "referee_notes": "yellow red", "operator": "or" } }
      ],
      "should": [
        { "match": { "referee_notes": "red" } }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

**Grading notes:** a real graded attempt (1.5/2) put the yellow/red condition in `filter` instead of `must` — `filter` doesn't contribute to scoring at all, and this query needs the match to contribute to the score so that `should` can further boost documents containing 'red'.
